Across four consecutive episodes, User Alex and the AI Wellness Companion tracked wellness metrics, while a separate fitness coaching session (User, Assistant) monitored athletic progression. In `therapy_chat_12_ep_001` (2025-01-06, sess_001, 42 mins), Alex reported mood 7/10, 7 hours sleep, and normal appetite. Alex deviated from normal Monday patterns by waking without grogginess and eating lunch (turkey/swiss/sourdough) at 14:08:55, contrasting with usual skipping. Alex resolved Jira ticket #4022 with Mike (14:06:38) and planned a Friday dinner with Sam. In `therapy_chat_12_ep_002` (2025-01-13, sess_002, 38 mins), Alex reported mood 6/10 and 6 hours sleep (woke once). Alex managed Product Launch Team Jira board #4045, faced a timeline disagreement, and planned a 1-hour yoga class for back tightness. Alex met Sam at the Pizza Place at 10:00:00 post-gym.

In `therapy_chat_12_dx_fitness_coaching_001` (2023-10-02, DC-001, 45 mins), User reported a motivated mood and completed a first 5k in 28 minutes, contrasting with a baseline six months ago where they walked 5 minutes after the first mile. User woke without an alarm, deviating from the normal pattern of hitting snooze three times. The Assistant asked about pace and feelings, repeating questions like "Did you feel like you wanted to run just a little bit less?" before truncation. In `therapy_chat_12_dx_fitness_coaching_002` (2023-10-09, DC-002, 52 mins), User reported an energetic mood. User ran 12 miles Sunday (1:52 finish, 9:20 pace) and increased weekly mileage to 25 miles. User increased sleep to 8 hours (bed 9:30 PM, wake 5:30 AM) and squats to 225lbs. User prioritized active recovery over still rest, contrasting with a previous month where adding 10 miles/week caused a 3-day limp. User plans a 12-week half-marathon starting November 1st (20 to 45 miles/week) with a goal under 2 hours. Assistant advised on shoe selection and nutrition strategy.", "metadata": {"type": "group_summary", "episode_ids": ["therapy_chat_12_ep_001", "therapy_chat_12_dx_fitness_coaching_001", "therapy_chat_12_ep_002", "therapy_chat_12_dx_fitness_coaching_002"]}}

